{
  "texts": [
    "These examples aid the model in adjusting its responses to better suit the particular task's requirements.",
    "Few-shot fine-tuning proves highly beneficial when we have limited resources with restricted task-specific data and aim to ensure the model generalizes effectively from these limited examples.",
    "Full fine-tuningFull fine-tuning involves training the model on a substantial dataset.",
    "This dataset is usually specific to the task or domain the model is intended to perform in.",
    "Full fine-tuning is more resource-intensive compared to few-shot fine-tuning and it requires more computational power and time, as the model needs to be trained over a larger set of data."
  ]
}